Therefore, the probability that edge `e` is present in `G ¤ë ÔŐö H ¤ë` is `p + q - p * q`. The parameter `¤â (¤â p * ¤â q)` simplifies to `1 - (1 - p) * (1 - q) = p + q - p * q`, which matches the desired probability.

