First, we should understand what `IsBinomialRandom` means. From the definition, `IsBinomialRandom G p P` means that `G` has the law `binomialRandom V p` with respect to `P`. So, `Measure.map G P = binomialRandom V p`.

Similarly, `Measure.map H P = binomialRandom V q`.

Now, we need to compute `Measure.map (fun ¤ë => G ¤ë ÔŐö H ¤ë) P`. By the definition of `map` for a function `f : ╬ę Ôćĺ X` and a measure `╬╝ : ╬ę Ôćĺ Set ╬▒ Ôćĺ Prop`, we have `map f ╬╝ S = ╬╝ {¤ë | f ¤ë Ôłł S}`.

